messages.content: Also values are higher

An extremely efficient card that deals reasonable damage, and gives a huge amount of temp hp. Keep in mind that nothing will modify the amount of temp hp gained (pen nib, strength, vigor, enemies having block, weak frail), you will always get exactly 12 (15). Great for keeping your calls online, and simply using it to "barricade" 12 (15) block between turns as a buffer for large enemy attacks makes it very worthy of being rare. You're getting 24 (30) points of output for just 2 energy, which compares very favorably to dash, and the temp hp is better than regular block. Like iron wave/dash, the mixed output of the card means that you can basically never draw it on the "wrong" turn, even more so since the block from this can be held over to future turns even if you aren't being attacked this turn.

It's an incredible pickup as a heart bonus at the start of the run, and is a valuable asset in every act of the game. It does really well into early hallway fights, and does very well into all 3 act 1 elites. It's usually a very safe pick as a boss reward, though you may need the scaling/engine effects of certain powers more. Even though it will be pretty expensive from a shop, It's still a solid pickup to just generally improve the consistency of your block. Great with snecko eye, strange spoon, and necronomicon. Upgrade is fantastic and one I prioritize very highly, a +6, with the +3 to the temp hp being particularly valuable to stay safe throughout the run. In all honesty, the numbers on this might be a bit too high, It would still be very good at 10 (13) for both effects.
Comparing it to <torch 6 temp hp exhaust> it is so much better
